MASTER SERVICES AGREEMENT (MSA #2026-SNIPP-ACME)

THIS MASTER SERVICES AGREEMENT (the "Agreement") is made and entered into as of May 01, 2026 (the "Effective Date"), by and between Snipp Corp, a Delaware corporation ("Customer"), and Acme Solutions Ltd, a United Kingdom private limited company ("Provider").

1. SCOPE OF SERVICES
Provider shall provide professional consultancy services, specifically focused on AI-driven legal technology implementations, as defined in various Statements of Work (SOWs) issued under this Agreement.

2. TERM AND TERMINATION
2.1 Initial Term: This Agreement shall remain in effect for three (3) years from the Effective Date.
2.2 Automatic Renewal: UNLESS TERMINATED as provided herein, this Agreement shall automatically renew for successive one (1) year periods. Either party must provide written notice of non-renewal at least ninety (90) days prior to the expiration of the then-current term.
2.3 Termination for Convenience: Customer may terminate this Agreement or any SOW for any reason upon sixty (60) days’ prior written notice to Provider.

3. FEES AND PAYMENT TERMS
3.1 Professional Fees: Customer shall pay Provider the fees set forth in each SOW.
3.2 Invoicing: Provider shall invoice Customer monthly. Payments are due within thirty (30) days of the invoice date (Net 30).
3.3 Late Payments: Interest shall accrue on late payments at the rate of 1.5% per month or the maximum rate permitted by law.

4. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY RIGHTS
4.1 Work Product: All deliverables and work product created by Provider specifically for Customer under this Agreement shall be considered "works made for hire" and shall be the sole and exclusive property of Customer.
4.2 Pre-existing IP: Provider retains ownership of any pre-existing tools, methodologies, or software used in performing the Services.

5. CONFIDENTIALITY & DATA PROTECTION
5.1 Confidential Information: The parties agree to keep all non-public information received from the other party strictly confidential.
5.2 Data Privacy: Both parties shall comply with all applicable data protection laws, including GDPR and CCPA. Provider shall implement industry-standard security measures to protect Customer Data.

6. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY
EXCEPT FOR BREACHES OF CONFIDENTIALITY OR INDEMNIFICATION OBLIGATIONS, NEITHER PARTY'S AGGREGATE LIABILITY SHALL EXCEED THE TOTAL FEES PAID BY CUSTOMER IN THE TWELVE (12) MONTHS PRECEDING THE CLAIM.

7. INDEMNIFICATION
Provider shall indemnify Customer against third-party claims alleging that the Services or Work Product infringe upon any third-party intellectual property rights.

8. GOVERNING LAW AND JURISDICTION
This Agreement shall be governed by the laws of the State of New York, without regard to its conflict of law principles. Any dispute shall be settled by binding arbitration in the City of New York.

9. MISCELLANEOUS
9.1 Force Majeure: Neither party shall be liable for delays caused by strikes, fires, floods, or other acts of God beyond their reasonable control.
9.2 Entire Agreement: This document constitutes the entire agreement between the parties and supersedes all prior discussions.

